  "body": "Given this Solidity code, `MyContract.sol`:\r\n\r\n```\r\ncontract MyContract {\r\n    modifier ownerOnly() {\r\n        require(msg.sender == _owner, \"You are not the owner\");\r\n        _;            // Assume this is line 100\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    function myMethod external ownerOnly {\r\n        require(false, \"Can't call this method\");\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nCalling `MyContract.myMethod()` results in a stack trace that contains:\r\n\r\n```\r\n     Error: VM Exception while processing transaction: reverted with reason string 'Can't call this method'\r\n      at MyContract.ownerOnly (contracts/main/MyContract.sol:100)\r\n```\r\n\r\nIn other words the revert message `Can't call this method` is correct, but the location of the revert is wrong (both the method `ownerOnly` and the line number `100` is wrong).",
