    "body": "Hmm, with this contract:\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\ncontract Foo {\r\n  address _owner;\r\n\r\n  modifier ownerOnly() {\r\n    require(msg.sender == _owner, \"You are not the owner\");\r\n    _;            // Assume this is line 100\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  function f() external ownerOnly {\r\n    require(false, \"Can't call this method\");\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nI get a stack trace like this:\r\n\r\n```\r\n    at Foo.ownerOnly (contracts/Foo.sol:8)\r\n    at Foo.f (contracts/Foo.sol:12)\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhere line 8 corresponds to `require(msg.sender == _owner, \"You are not the owner\");` and line 12 to `function f() external ownerOnly {`, which seems correct?\r\n\r\nI'm using solc 0.8.9 and the optimizer is disabled.\r\n\r\n@lukehutch @vulntor maybe you have the optimizer enabled? In that case, the line numbers can be off.",
