    "body": "@fvictorio I should have specified, the test `msg.sender == _owner` should succeed (since in the original report, the error was \"Can't call this method\" not \"You are not the owner\"). To simplify the code:\r\n\r\n```\r\ncontract Foo {\r\n  address _owner;\r\n\r\n  modifier ownerOnly() {\r\n    // The following test is commented out\r\n    // require(msg.sender == _owner, \"You are not the owner\");\r\n    _;            // Assume this is line 100\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  function f() external ownerOnly {\r\n    require(false, \"Can't call this method\");\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe error will be shown with the location `_;` (\"line 100\" as labeled).\r\n\r\nAdditionally, the calling context (one stack frame deeper) does not always show in the stack trace when there is a revert. Often only the top stack frame shows, or the caller stack frame does not show. Yes, that could be an optimizer issue.",
